'''史蒂芬·索特洛夫'''{{BD|1983年|5月11日|2014年|9月2日|catIdx=Sotloff}}，[[美國|美國]]自由撰稿记者，2013年在[[敘利亞|敘利亞]]被[[伊斯蘭國|伊斯蘭國]]（Islamic State）綁架，2014年被該組織的[[聖戰士約翰|聖戰士約翰]][[斬首|斬首]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=ISIS video shows beheading of Steven Sotloff|url=https://www.cnn.com/2014/09/02/world/meast/isis-american-journalist-sotloff/index.html|access-date=2021-07-10|last=CNN|first=By Chelsea J. Carter and Ashley Fantz|work=CNN|archive-date=2021-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210710162343/https://www.cnn.com/2014/09/02/world/meast/isis-american-journalist-sotloff/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

索特洛夫是[[美國猶太人|美國猶太人]]，生於[[邁阿密|邁阿密]]，為《[[時代周刊|時代周刊]]》、《[[基督教科學箴言報|基督教科學箴言報]]》、《[[外交政策雜誌|外交政策雜誌]]》及《[[世界事務雙月刊|世界事務雙月刊]]》工作，專門採訪中東情勢。 2014年3月於[[敘利亞|敘利亞]][[阿勒坡|阿勒坡]]被伊斯蘭國武裝分子綁架。2014年伊斯蘭國將其斬首，並發布實況影片<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/iraq/11071159/Steven-Sotloff-beheaded-by-Islamic-State-live.html |title=Steven Sotloff 'beheaded by Islamic State' – latest |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |author=Raf Sanchez |date=September 2, 2014 |access-date=September 2, 2014 |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902183333/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/iraq/11071159/Steven-Sotloff-beheaded-by-Islamic-State-live.html |archive-date=2014-09-02 |url-status=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/After-James-Foley-ISIS-beheads-another-US-journalist-Steven-Sotloff/articleshow/41551162.cms | title=After James Foley, ISIS beheads another US journalist Steven Sotloff | newspaper=The Times of India | date=September 3, 2014 | access-date=September 3, 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903063623/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/After-James-Foley-ISIS-beheads-another-US-journalist-Steven-Sotloff/articleshow/41551162.cms | archive-date=2014-09-03 | url-status=no }}</ref>。索特洛夫被斩首后，美国总统奥巴马表示，美国将采取行动，削弱和摧毁ISIS<ref>{{cite news | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/World/US/Obama-says-beheading-videos-wont-intimidate-US/articleshow/41606325.cms | title=Obama says beheading videos won't intimidate US | newspaper=The Times of India | date=September 3, 2014 | access-date=September 4, 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904082211/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/Obama-says-beheading-videos-wont-intimidate-US/articleshow/41606325.cms | archive-date=2014-09-04 | url-status=no }}</ref>。

2015年6月24日，奥巴马总统当着索特洛夫家族和其他人质家属的面签署了一项行政命令，彻底改革被ISIS等组织扣押在国外的美国人质解救方式<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2015/06/24/statement-president-us-governments-hostage-policy-review|title=Statement by the President on the U.S. Government's Hostage Policy Review|date=2015-06-24|access-date=2016-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211165202/https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2015/06/24/statement-president-us-governments-hostage-policy-review|archive-date=2017-02-11|via=[[NARA|National Archives]]|work=[[whitehouse.gov|whitehouse.gov]]|url-status=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/watch-obama-announce-new-hostage-policy-n381011|title=Obama Announces Change in Hostage Policy|access-date=2016-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115203543/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/watch-obama-announce-new-hostage-policy-n381011|archive-date=2018-11-15|url-status=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/06/23/politics/hostage-policy-review-changes-white-house/index.html|title=White House says more than 30 Americans held hostage|author1-link=Jeremy Diamond (journalist)|author1=Jeremy Diamond|author2=Sunlen Serfaty|website=CNN|access-date=2016-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191115211214/https://www.cnn.com/2015/06/23/politics/hostage-policy-review-changes-white-house/index.html|archive-date=2019-11-15|url-status=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/24/world/obama-ordering-changes-in-us-hostage-policies.html|title=Obama Ordering Changes in U.S. Hostage Policies|last=Davis|first=Julie Hirschfeld|date=2015-06-23|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2016-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003230041/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/24/world/obama-ordering-changes-in-us-hostage-policies.html|archive-date=2019-10-03|url-status=no}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=The White House|title=The President